## Render Deployment Config

```yaml
# render.yaml — taruh di root repo
services:
  - type: web
    name: renn-portfolio
    runtime: python
    buildCommand: "./build.sh"
    startCommand: "gunicorn config.wsgi:application"
    envVars:
      - key: DJANGO_SETTINGS_MODULE
        value: config.settings.production
      - key: SECRET_KEY
        generateValue: true
      - key: DEBUG
        value: false
      - key: DATABASE_URL
        fromDatabase:
          name: renn-portfolio-db
          property: connectionString
      - key: ALLOWED_HOSTS
        value: renn-portfolio.onrender.com

databases:
  - name: renn-portfolio-db
    databaseName: renn_portfolio
    user: renn
```

```bash
# build.sh
#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -o errexit
pip install -r requirements.txt
python manage.py collectstatic --noinput --settings=config.settings.production
python manage.py migrate --settings=config.settings.production
```

### Render vs Vercel — kenapa lebih simple:
- Tidak perlu `vercel-wsgi` adapter
- PostgreSQL tersedia built-in via Render Managed Database
- `gunicorn` jalan sebagai persistent web service (bukan serverless/cold start)
- Static files: WhiteNoise tetap dipakai, tapi tanpa workaround routing khusus
- Auto-deploy dari GitHub push ke `main` branch

